<TITLE> ICB MD made SEC chief </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 3 (bdnews24.com)Md Ziaul Haque Khondker has become the first investment banker in Bangladesh to head the stocks regulator Securities and Exchange Commission. An establishment ministry circular on Sunday announced the appointment of the managing director of the state-run Investment Corporation of Bangladesh as the seventh chairman of the market watchdog for three years. A Dhaka University economics graduate of the 1973 -74 batch, Zia began his career in the capital market as a research officer in the ICB in 1977. His appointment as the new head of the SEC comes after the retirement of Faruq Ahmad Siddiqi on March 19. Siddiqi took over as the sixth chairman on March 15, 2006. In 1996, he was promoted and transferred to Bangladesh Shilpa Rin Sangstha as general manager. Zia returned to the ICB as general manager in1998 and was made its managing director in 2000.
